    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Interface2" translate="true">TOP-TIP #1</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">When you start using </text><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">MotionDesigner</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">, it is easy to end up with a very short-segment that you do not know is part of a motion.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">To find a very short </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">segment</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> that you cannot see in the motion graphs, click the </text><text styleclass="Parameter" translate="true">Next</text><image src="Red-14-4.gif" imagestyleclass="Default" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> button, to move the Selected-Segment through the complete motion. If the </text><text styleclass="Parameter" translate="true">Blend-Point number</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> increases by 1, but you cannot see the </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Selected-Segment</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> in the motion graphs, then you have found a very short segment that you may not want in your motion. Click the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Tools-DeleteSegment" styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Delete Segment</link><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> button to remove the very short segment.</text></para>
  </body>
